Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Pour sweetened condensed milk into 9-inch pie plate. Cover with foil; place in larger shallow baking pan. Pour hot water into larger pan to depth of 1-inch. Bake 1 hour or until thick and caramel-colored. Beat until smooth. Cool 1 hour. Refrigerate until serving time. Serve as dip with assorted dippers. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator for up to 1 week.